subSubSection.paragraph:
Abdomen black with dark grey dusting, dorsum slightly brownish dusted, subshining in different angles of view. Abdominal hairs black. Hind marginal bristles generally fine, short; tergum 5 with long bristles; tergum 6 with long, thick bristles; tergum 7 very short, spine-like bristles. Sternum 8 with long, dense black hairs (
Fig. 2
). Genitalia (
Figs. 3–5
) very enlarged especially lateral lamella. Anterior parts of hypandrium and lateral lamella (epandrial lamella) shiny, former dorsally convex at tip, latter globular with claw-shaped apical projection.
